What is the projected market size & growth rate of the In-Station Passenger Information System Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

In-station passenger information system market size is valued at USD 52,850 million by 2028 is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate of 12.60% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on in-station passenger information system provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecasted period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth.

Passenger information system is a kind of electronic information system that provides audio and visual information to passengers and also presents the ability to track, monitor and manage the real-time passenger information. The information collected by the passenger information system completely relies on the project requirement and can be communicated via loudspeakers and screens.

The increasing frequency of passenger journey through public transport has been directly influencing the growth of in-station passenger information system market over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Also the rising use of smartphones with better connectivity improves the transit experience which is also flourishing the growth of the in-station passenger information system market. In addition, the rising demands for real-time, consistent and reliable passenger information as well as ever-increasing implementation of advanced technologies such as big data, cloud and IoT for the development of such systems to enhance the general experience of the passenger are also positively impacting the growth of the market. Furthermore, the high adoption of such systems amongst the transit agencies leading to the development of passenger satisfaction and comfort are also largely lifting the growth of the in-station passenger information system market.

However, the high maintenance and implementation costs of these systems are acting as the major limitations for the growth of in-station passenger information system in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028, whereas the outmoded infrastructure and meager internet connectivity across underdeveloped economies have the potential to challenge the growth of the in-station passenger information system market.

Likewise, the high adoption of IoT and big data to improve passenger travel experiences along with execution of digital devices and ICT solutions so as to deal with the city efficiently will further cater ample new opportunities that will lead to the growth of the in-station passenger information system market in the above mentioned forecasted period.

